entry.title: Rip Current Statement issued February 9 at 9:45PM AST until February 13 at 6:00PM AST by NWS San Juan PR
entry.summary:
* WHAT...Life-threatening rip currents due to large breaking waves of up to 8 to 9 feet, increasing up to 14 feet on Sunday.
* WHERE...Beaches from Aguada and Rincon in western Puerto Rico eastward across the north coast to Fajardo and Ceiba in eastern Puerto Rico and further east to Culebra and Saint Thomas.
* WHEN...Through Tuesday afternoon.
* IMPACTS...Rip currents that can sweep even the best swimmers away from shore into deeper water where it becomes difficult to return to safety. High waves that can wash over jetties and sweep people and pets onto jagged rocks. Large breaking waves generating hazardous coastal conditions and localized breach erosion.

entry.title: Flood Warning issued February 9 at 8:38PM EST until February 10 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
entry.summary:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida...
St Johns River Near Astor affecting Volusia and Lake Counties.
.The Saint Johns River near Astor remains right around Minor Flood Stage this evening. It is forecast to fall below Minor Flood Stage tonight into early Saturday morning, with the river continuing to decline while in Action Stage through the weekend. The river is then expected to fall below Action Stage early next week.
For the St. Johns River...including Astor...Minor flooding is forecast.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.
The next statement will be issued Saturday morning at 700 AM EST.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...St Johns River near Astor.
* WHEN...Until tomorrow morning.
* IMPACTS...At 2.3 feet, Many docks become submerged along the river and in canals in the Astor community. Water enters yards of properties on Bartram Road, Holiday Circle and along Wild Hog Road on the Lake County side. In Volusia County, water encroaches yards of homes on the river side of Alice Drive. No wake zones are in effect from near the South Moon Canal to approximately 800 feet south of the Riverview lodge.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:30 PM EST Friday the stage was 2.3 feet. - Bankfull stage is 2.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:30 PM EST Friday was 2.4 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage tonight into Saturday, continue declining through Action Stage this weekend, and then fall below Action Stage early next week. - Flood stage is 2.3 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood

entry.title: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 3:42PM AKST until February 9 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
entry.summary:
...IMPACTFUL SNOW CONTINUES INTO THE WEEKEND...
.Widespread moderate precipitation continues across the NE gulf coast and majority of the panhandle. With cold air in place, precipitation started as snow before gradually transitioning to a mix as the surface front turns winds more southerly and brings up surface temperatures. Any stalling of the surface front for the Icy Strait corridor or northern inner channels will lead to later transition to a more rain heavy mix, resulting in greater storm total snow accumulation overnight and into Saturday. Stay tuned for the latest forecast information on this complex system.
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to two inches.
* WHERE...Glacier Bay and Eastern Chichagof Island.
* WHEN...Until 9 PM AKST this evening.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snowfall rates will continue to diminish late this evening and into the overnight hours.
